---
title: Soy & Orange Pork with Mediterranean Vegetables and Couscous
description: Soy sauce is a crucial ingredient for almost any Chinese cooking but today we're bringing a little bit of its oriental, umami magic to a more Mediterranean dish. Orange adds a taste of sunshine and the veggies keep things fresh. Enjoy!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/soy-orange-pork-e09f47a2-74c79df1.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/soy-orange-pork-59390ab9171c585cfe4cc342-868b9546.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/soy-orange-pork-59390ab9171c585cfe4cc342
author: Mimi Morley
course: main course
cuisine: Mediterranean
nutrition:
  calories: 574 kcal
  fat: 14 g
  saturated fat: 5 g
  carbohydrates: 69 g
  sugar: 15 g
  protein: 41 g
  sodium: 3 g
  serving size: 531
servings: 2
time required: 40 minutes
---

Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Zest and juice the @orange{1/2}. Put both the zest and juice in a #mixing bowl{}. Add the @soy sauce{25%ml} and the @sugar{1}. Mix together, then add the @British pork loin steaks{2} and make sure it is well coated in the marinade. Set aside to marinate while you prepare everything else.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm pieces. Trim the @courgette{1} then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into 2cm pieces. Put the pepper and courgette on a lined #baking tray{} and drizzle with @oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until soft and slightly charred, ~{25-30%minutes}. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1/2%bunch} (stalks and all).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #small saucepan{} on medium heat and add the onion. Stir and cook until soft, ~{10%minutes}. Add the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml}, lower the heat and cook gently until the onion is caramelised, another ~{10%minutes}.

> TIP: Stir every now and then to make sure the onions aren't burning.

When done, put a lid on the saucepan, take it off the heat and set aside.

Meanwhile, pour the @water{300%ml} into a large #saucepan{} and add the @chicken stock powder{1/2%tsp}. Bring to the boil. When boiling, stir to dissolve the stock powder then stir in the @couscous{150%g}, pop a lid on the saucepan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{8-10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Put a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Lay in the pork (leave the marinade in the bowl for now). Cook until slightly caramelised, ~{7-8%minutes} on each side.

> TIP: The pork is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Remove from the frying pan and rest on a #board{} for a few minutes. Cover with @foil{} to keep warm. Add the marinade to your (now empty) frying pan and simmer for ~{2%minutes}.

Fluff up the couscous with a #fork{}. Add the roasted veggies, the caramelised onion and half the parsley. Stir everything together. Slice your pork into roughly 1cm thick slices. Serve the couscous in #bowls{} with the pork on top. Drizzle with a good spoonful of soy and orange sauce and sprinkle on the remaining parsley. Enjoy!